00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:51,100
=Lucky's First Love=

2
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:53,860
=Episode 1=

3
00:02:08,380 --> 00:02:09,420
A cup of espresso please.

4
00:02:25,620 --> 00:02:27,660
Mr. Xia, your schedule for today is as follows:

5
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:29,300
9am, Teleconference;

6
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:31,380
10am, monthly report by the Planning Department;

7
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:34,060
12pm, lunch meeting with technical directors,

8
00:02:35,020 --> 00:02:35,740
and Mr. Chen of the advertising company

9
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:37,260
has made an appointment with you
on the race course at 2pm.

10
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:38,060
I see.

11
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:40,980
Mr. Xia, are you going to take her with you?

12
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:42,220
Of course.

13
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:43,180
Take care on the road.

14
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:50,500
Your phone is ringing.

15
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:52,860
Thank you, madam.

16
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:55,560
(Reply at once)

17
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:00,740
Hello, Mr. Xia.

18
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:01,460
Where are you?

19
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:03,020
I'm near the company.

20
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:04,540
Come over right now.

21
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:11,900
Here it goes again.

22
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:16,700
Excuse me, would you move aside please?

23
00:03:17,580 --> 00:03:18,580
Well, who are you?

24
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:19,260
Mr. Xia.

25
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:28,260
Mr. Xia, I drove into your car carelessly.

26
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,900
Shall I buy you a cup of coffee?

27
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,820
Mr. Xia, you see,

28
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:38,420
we go to work in the same building,

29
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:39,700
and I drove into your car today,

30
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:41,860
which is kind of a predestined bond.

31
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:43,340
Or

32
00:03:43,940 --> 00:03:45,060
shall we do it this way, Mr. Xia?

33
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:46,820
Miss,

34
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:47,980
he's my boss.

35
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:49,780
You can talk about things related to the car with me.

36
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:51,700
What can I say to you?

37
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:52,820
It's not your car.

38
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:06,180
You are his employee, so you should have his number.

39
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:08,700
Do it this way. Give his number to me,

40
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:09,860
and I'll contact him myself.

41
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:11,740
Judging from the position of collision,
you should bear full responsibility for it.

42
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:13,220
The paint here has been scraped off,

43
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:14,700
and the reflector has to be changed as well.

44
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,100
How would you like to deal with it?

45
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:18,100
We'll report to the police
if you'd like to go through insurance.

46
00:04:18,380 --> 00:04:19,420
If you'd like to settle it privately,

47
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:21,300
it'll cost at least 10,000 yuan to repair the car.

48
00:04:21,820 --> 00:04:22,780
10,000 yuan?

49
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,700
Besides, this does not include

50
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:28,140
the loss of delaying my boss' use
of the car during the repair.

51
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:29,940
I don't think

52
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:31,660
he'll fuss about this with me.

53
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,380
Maybe it'll be OK if I buy him a cup of coffee.

54
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:42,460
He can't be so vulgar, can he?

55
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,380
Just a moment, just a moment.

56
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:52,140
Just a moment.

57
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:55,900
Mr. Xia. Thanks, Mr. Xia.

58
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,420
Mr. Xia, haven't you gone upstairs yet?

59
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:03,860
Oh, by the way, I've settled the collision accident.

60
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:18,940
Well, Mr. Xia,

61
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,580
actually when it comes to cars,

62
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:22,940
you can directly ask people in the Admin Department

63
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,340
or other male colleagues next time.

64
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,540
They know more about cars than I do.

65
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:27,740
You are near.

66
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:32,740
You are right.

67
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,300
I'm Xing Yun, and my English name is Lucky.

68
00:05:41,460 --> 00:05:42,460
I'm 24 this year.

69
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:44,660
The man beside me is my boss Xia Ke,

70
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,860
CEO of TIG, a famous mobile game company.

71
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:49,060
There is a lot to like about him.

72
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:52,380
For example, he has a discerning eye for talent
and is good at choosing the right persons for jobs.

73
00:05:55,580 --> 00:05:58,420
Xing Yun, that's a lucky name.

74
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:00,980
You're the one.

75
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:03,420
Please.

76
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:04,460
He's very affable

77
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,860
and often invites employees to his home.

78
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,900
Don't go out if you can't
finish modifying the sketches.

79
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:12,060
Mr. Xia!

80
00:06:12,980 --> 00:06:14,940
Mr. Xia, I've got to go to the bathroom.

81
00:06:16,060 --> 00:06:18,380
He shows solicitude and consideration for his employees.

82
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:23,220
Mr. Xia, why is it all spicy food?

83
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,300
Dip it in water before eating.

84
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:29,340
Morning, Mr. Xia.

85
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:30,020
Morning.

86
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:30,580
Morning, Mr. Xia.

87
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:34,860
He has good temper and never throws a fit.

88
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:37,460
Mr. Xia, this is the latest modified version
of character setting.

89
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:41,900
Do it again!

90
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:43,620
OK. I'll modify it now.

91
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,220
All right. I'll take this one back.

92
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:47,180
Morning, Xing Yun.

93
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:47,780
Morning.

94
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:50,380
In any case, over the past two years,

95
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,940
TIG has created

96
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:54,500
an industry-wide phenomenal game
Infinite Unknown Love

97
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:57,180
and become the most promising mobile game company
in the industry.

98
00:06:57,540 --> 00:07:00,060
Xia Ke is a once-in-a-lifetime genius boss,

99
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:02,300
and for us employees who are on board

100
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,500
the express cruise liner en route
to our ambitions,

101
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:06,020
what justification do we have
to complain about him?

102
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:06,580
Morning.

103
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:07,220
Morning.

104
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:26,980
Magnitude-7 earthquake, isn't it?

105
00:07:28,460 --> 00:07:30,580
The targets are all from
your Planning Department.

106
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:35,100
I reckon he's not happy with the plan
for instance zones again.

107
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:38,420
Instance zones? Has the development
of instance zones kicked off at last?

108
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:39,460
Yes.

109
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:41,860
Mr. Xia pays special attention to
the development of instance zones this time,

110
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:44,060
but there has been little progress all along.

111
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,860
I heard they'll start
a company-wide competitive selection

112
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,140
if there are still no good plans.

113
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:49,940
What does it mean?

114
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:52,300
Whoever in the company can make good suggestions

115
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:53,780
can take charge of this plan.

116
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:55,940
Even a cleaning lady has a chance.

117
00:08:00,420 --> 00:08:01,940
Xing Yun, what are you thinking?

118
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,660
I was thinking if I'll stand a chance.

119
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:08,900
Aren't you always interested in

120
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:10,020
game design and planning?

121
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:10,820
Give it a try.

122
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,900
If you can take charge of planning
for the instance zones,

123
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,220
your pay will be doubled.

124
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,580
But I'm just a small-time original animation artist.

125
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:19,860
There are so many capable people in the company.
Can it be my turn?

126
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:21,540
You are the first employee of TIG,

127
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,900
his meritorious courtier, his comrade-in-arms!

128
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:31,820
He's here, he's here. Look!

129
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:37,620
Look, he's so handsome!

130
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:38,900
So manly!

131
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:41,140
Be my boyfriend.

132
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:41,860
True enough.

133
00:08:43,260 --> 00:08:44,180
Wake up, girls.

134
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:46,420
Nowadays there are no princes and knights.

135
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:47,580
There is only one kind of man
who rides a white horse -

136
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:49,100
a beast dressed in human clothes.

137
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:58,140
You are the most handsome, boss.

138
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:00,260
Which one would you like,
iced sweet-sour plum juice or coffee?

139
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:02,020
This one.

140
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:10,460
Mr. Xia,

141
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,740
let's find a time to sign the contract.

142
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:15,620
Mr. Chen, let me do some math for you.

143
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:16,940
I've seen the ads for

144
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:18,580
your VR game device.

145
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:20,620
For the social platform you've chosen
for advertising placement,

146
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:22,980
active male users account for 48% of the total,

147
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:24,540
of which men aged between 20-40

148
00:09:24,620 --> 00:09:25,620
account for about 60%.

149
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:27,300
And of those, no more than 20%

150
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:28,420
would really spend 3,000 yuan

151
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:29,460
on a VR device,

152
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,140
so your probability of reaching actual buyers
can only come to

153
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:35,020
57.6% of your expected value,

154
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,420
even below the passing mark.

155
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,660
From what I can see
in your company's advertising placement,

156
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:40,900
I think you should lower your quoted price

157
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:42,220
by around 15%.

158
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:47,860
You are really a sharp-nosed man, Mr. Xia.

159
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:50,380
I never set my eyes on stunts.

160
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:52,220
Take choosing a horse for example.

161
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:54,100
The horse I choose may not have shiny hair

162
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:55,980
or outstanding appearance,

163
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:57,300
but I can see

164
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:58,500
the tenacious, unyielding characters in it,

165
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,980
and it can always help me win a race.

166
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:05,420
OK.

167
00:10:06,260 --> 00:10:07,300
I can't convince you, Mr. Xia.

168
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:10,140
Let's do it this way.
Ride on your unyielding horse

169
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:12,060
and race with me on the racetrack.

170
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:14,500
The winner will have the final say.
What do you think?

171
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:49,340
Alas,

172
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:54,340
Mr. Xia, my horse is not in a good condition today.

173
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:56,420
I'm willing to throw in the towel.

174
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:59,100
I'll have the contract sent to you tomorrow.

175
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:01,060
I've got things to do later.

176
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:02,260
Let's make an appointment some other day.

177
00:11:03,020 --> 00:11:03,180
OK.

178
00:11:04,220 --> 00:11:04,940
Bye.

179
00:11:10,060 --> 00:11:13,340
Mr. Xia, you really have a heroic bearing
and a flair for both the pen and the sword.

180
00:11:18,460 --> 00:11:20,180
Mr. Chen is so slippery.

181
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:21,500
It's plain as day
that he has quoted an unreasonable price,

182
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:23,380
but he's only willing to reduce it
after making a bet with us.

183
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,900
It's a pity that he's not good at choosing horses.

184
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:31,140
Mr. Xia,

185
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:34,060
I heard the instance zones project
for Infinite Unknown Love is about to kick off

186
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:35,700
and you are going to have
a company-wide competitive selection for ideas.

187
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:36,540
Is it true?

188
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:37,300
What do you mean?

189
00:11:38,020 --> 00:11:39,220
Actually I've

190
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:40,740
been taking courses in game design.

191
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:42,580
I'm very interested in this project.

192
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:44,700
I've drawn up a draft plan.

193
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:45,900
Let me get it for you.

194
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:51,260
Do you have to

195
00:11:51,340 --> 00:11:52,860
save me with such an idol drama-style posture?

196
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:54,900
Don't you watch where you are going?

197
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,340
Thanks, Mr. Xia.

198
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:04,380
Could it be his confession of love next?

199
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:17,420
You are my little lucky star which can only
be found by serendipity,

200
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:21,580
of course I'll protect you at all costs.

201
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:26,300
Mr. Xia.

202
00:12:38,140 --> 00:12:38,660
Ah!

203
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:40,540
Have you ever been in a relationship?

204
00:12:41,180 --> 00:12:41,700
Ah?

205
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:44,380
Aren't you asking while knowing the answer?

206
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:45,700
You are going beyond your depth!

207
00:12:46,260 --> 00:12:47,660
Well, what has whether I've been
in a relationship or not

208
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:48,700
to do with my work?

209
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:50,140
I have a strong feeling about this game,

210
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:51,100
I can give all my time

211
00:12:51,140 --> 00:12:52,340
to this game,

212
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:52,860
I think...

213
00:12:56,020 --> 00:12:57,260
If you want to do the instance zones of the game,

214
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,180
firstly, you must find a man
who's willing to date you.

215
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:02,820
Ah?

216
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,620
Isn't it just dating?

217
00:13:10,260 --> 00:13:12,020
What's great about it?

218
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:19,700
Wrong password.

219
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:22,260
What's Xing Yun's password?

220
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,860
3732.

221
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:26,500
Wrong password.

222
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:29,500
Xing Yun, 373258.

223
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:30,700
Yes, yes, yes, it's this one.

224
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:33,380
373258.

225
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:35,380
Thanks.

226
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:36,060
Thanks...

227
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:39,460
Mr. Xia.

228
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,500
Where has she gone?

229
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:47,860
She... she was not feeling well,
so she went home first.

230
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:52,140
By the way, what is the company's regulation for

231
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:53,260
clocking in and out for others?

232
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:53,980
Ah?

233
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:56,220
Deduct 1 month bonus.

234
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,900
Don't do that, Mr. Xia, just this once.

235
00:13:59,460 --> 00:14:00,540
Make it dock the year-end bonus.

236
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:03,140
No, no, no.

237
00:14:03,740 --> 00:14:04,580
Xing Yun is going on a blind date.

238
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,100
With a young talent who works for a bank

239
00:14:06,140 --> 00:14:07,420
and was introduced to her by her older cousin sister
upon her mother's request.

240
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:08,780
This is all I know.

241
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:10,740
Mr. Xia, be sure not to dock my year-end bonus.

242
00:14:10,780 --> 00:14:12,060
I'll never dare to do it again next time.

243
00:14:14,140 --> 00:14:14,580
A blind date?

244
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:17,380
Is she really going?

245
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:25,340
Miss Xing Cheng,
you've been nagging all the way.

246
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:26,500
Haven't I told you?

247
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,860
I promised to go on a blind date
simply for the sake of...

248
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:31,220
work.

249
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:38,820
Are you Xing Yun?

250
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:41,340
Hello, I'm Chu Nan.

251
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,060
Hello.

252
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:44,260
What would you like to drink?

253
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,740
You needn't. I can buy one for myself.

254
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,220
Let's give a formal introduction of ourselves.

255
00:14:50,820 --> 00:14:52,980
My name is Chu Nan. Nan as in Nanmu phoebe.

256
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:55,660
My name is Xing Yun, yun for luck.

257
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:57,180
A very pleasant name.

258
00:14:57,860 --> 00:14:58,340
Thanks.

259
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:01,020
Are you a native here?

260
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:02,580
What about you?

261
00:15:03,220 --> 00:15:04,340
My ancestral hometown is Sichuan.

262
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:07,700
Sichuan abounds in Nanmu phoebe, do you know?

263
00:15:08,660 --> 00:15:09,860
My grandfather is a Sichuan native,

264
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:10,900
also a carpenter.

265
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:13,060
That's why he gave me this name.

266
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:16,660
A very pleasant name.

267
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:18,940
You are the first one to give such a response

268
